column7: 603641: I feel comfortable reading, analyzing, and reacting to journal reports on clinical trials.
column9: 603642: I have previous experience working with or around clinical trials.
column11: 603643: I feel I can critically evaluate a trial and point out any flaws in design or interpretation.
column13: 603644: I know the purpose of a clinical trial and can describe the pros and cons of this type of research methodology as compared to others.
column15: 603645: It is important to consider non-clinical factors such as socioeconomic status and where a research subject lives when designing a clinical trial and enrolling research subjects.
column17: 603646: I feel I can take the principles I have learned in other courses (biostatistics, research methodology, etc) and apply them to clinical trials today.
column19: 603647: I fully understand the role of ethics committees, HIPAA, and Data Safety Monitoring Boards in the oversight of clinical trials.
column21: 603648: I feel I can discern the level of impact a trial will have on the health community overall given the quality of the trial methodology.
